1
00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:05,136
<i>FLETCHER RIDGE, ILLINOIS. LARGE</i>
<i>ENOUGH TO HAVE A U.P.S. OFFICE,</i>

2
00:00:05,205 --> 00:00:07,372
AND A DRIVER NAMED
JAROD HARPER.

3
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,808
VERY GOOD, BROOTS.
ANY PHYSICAL DESCRIPTION?

4
00:00:09,876 --> 00:00:12,344
SIZE, WEIGHT AND COLOR
ALL MATCH JAROD PERFECTLY.

5
00:00:12,413 --> 00:00:15,914
<i>AND HE GOT THE JOB AT ALMOST</i>
<i>EXACTLY THE SAME TIME THAT...</i>

6
00:00:15,983 --> 00:00:18,716
- I CALCULATED HIS POSITION.
- CALL LYLE.

7
00:00:18,785 --> 00:00:21,520
- I ALREADY HAVE.
HE'S ON HIS WAY.
-<i> GREAT. LET'S GO.</i>

8
00:00:21,589 --> 00:00:24,055
[ Cell Phone Rings,
Beeps ]

9
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:26,057
WHAT?
[ Mr. Parker ]
ANGEL.

10
00:00:26,126 --> 00:00:28,760
ANGEL, I HAVE TO SEE YOU.
[ Whispering ]
DADDY?

11
00:00:28,828 --> 00:00:32,698
THE JUNKYARD NEAR
THE QUENTIN STREET OVERPASS,
AND HURRY.

12
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:35,700
DADDY!
[ Dial Tone ]

13
00:00:35,770 --> 00:00:38,002
<i> YOU LOOK BOTHERED,</i>
<i> MISS PARKER.</i>

14
00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:41,172
DON'T YOU HAVE
A BAKE SALE TO ORGANIZE?

15
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:43,175
<i> I KNOW THESE ARE</i>
<i> STRESSFUL TIMES FOR YOU.</i>

16
00:00:43,243 --> 00:00:45,310
THAT'S WHY I WANT YOU
TO HAVE THIS.

17
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,380
IT'S A PRAYER CARD.
I SLEPT WITH IT
UNDER MY PILLOW.

18
00:00:50,684 --> 00:00:53,318
- THAT EXPLAINS
THE GREASE STAINS.
- I ASKED FOR IT TO BE FILLED...

19
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:56,054
WITH THE ANSWERS YOU NEED.

20
00:00:56,122 --> 00:00:59,558
- GOD BLESS.
- YOU TOO.

21
00:01:05,298 --> 00:01:07,299
PARKER?
ARE YOU COMING?

22
00:01:08,736 --> 00:01:10,735
I'LL BE BACK.

23
00:01:10,804 --> 00:01:12,938
WHAT ABOUT JAROD?
WHAT ABOUT LYLE?

24
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:17,075
UM, BUY ME SOME TIME.
A FEW HOURS.

25
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:20,178
<i>[ Siren Wails ]</i>

26
00:01:21,515 --> 00:01:25,050
[ Second Siren Wailing ]

27
00:01:29,823 --> 00:01:31,823
OUCH!

28
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:36,227
<i> SORRY, MISTER.</i>
<i> IT GOT AWAY FROM ME.</i>

29
00:01:36,296 --> 00:01:40,031
WOW.
THIS IS A GREAT CAR.
THANKS.

30
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,100
I BOUGHT IT
WITH MY TOOTH FAIRY MONEY.
"TOOTH FAIRY"?

31
00:01:42,169 --> 00:01:44,703
YOU KNOW, WHERE YOU PUT
YOUR TOOTH UNDER YOUR PILLOW,

32
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,738
THE TOOTH FAIRY TAKES IT
AND LEAVES YOU MONEY.

33
00:01:46,806 --> 00:01:49,007
DIDN'T YOU EVER GET THAT
WHEN YOU WERE A KID?

34
00:01:49,076 --> 00:01:51,743
I WASN'T REALLY A KID
WHEN I WAS A KID.

35
00:01:51,812 --> 00:01:54,613
THANKS, MISTER.

36
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:57,082
<i>[ Bell Tolling ]</i>

37
00:01:57,151 --> 00:01:59,818
[ Woman ]
WOULD YOU JUST SHUT UP? I DON'T
WANT TO TALK ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.

38
00:01:59,886 --> 00:02:02,220
DAMN IT, SARAH,
WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

39
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:04,923
CAM, WE DON'T NEED TO BE
MAKING THESE ARRANGEMENTS.

40
00:02:04,991 --> 00:02:07,992
THE HELL WE DON'T!
THESE PEOPLE AT THE HOSPITAL
ALREADY SHOWED...

41
00:02:08,061 --> 00:02:10,562
THEY DON'T CARE WHETHER
US LARSENS LIVE OR DIE--
BILLY, COME ON.

42
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:13,799
-<i> CAM, THE DOCTORS SAID--</i>
- I KNOW WHAT THE DOCTORS SAID.

43
00:02:13,868 --> 00:02:17,235
I KNOW WHAT
NEEDS TO BE DONE.

44
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:19,638
-<i> WHY DO YOU HAVE GUNS?</i>
- [ Engine Revs ]

45
00:02:19,707 --> 00:02:23,475
CAM! WHAT ARE YOU
PLANNING TO DO?

46
00:02:23,544 --> 00:02:26,645
- I DIDN'T START THIS, SARAH.
- CAMERON!

47
00:02:26,714 --> 00:02:28,313
GO HOME!
[ Screams ]

48
00:02:37,691 --> 00:02:40,159
COME ON, DAMN IT!

49
00:02:41,595 --> 00:02:43,595
[ Crying ]
DAMN IT!

50
00:02:44,598 --> 00:02:46,798
<i> HERE YOU GO.</i>

51
00:02:48,602 --> 00:02:50,602
USE MINE.

52
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,976
[ Beeps, Dials ]

53
00:02:58,045 --> 00:03:01,012
[ Line Ringing ]
[ Woman ]
9-1-1. CAN I HELP YOU?

54
00:03:01,081 --> 00:03:03,247
YES, MA'AM. MY NAME
IS SARAH LARSEN.

55
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:06,318
MY BROTHERS ARE ON THE WAY
TO THE HOSPITAL. THEY HAVE GUNS.

56
00:03:06,387 --> 00:03:08,853
<i>I DON'T KNOW!</i>
<i>LOOK, YOU JUST</i>
<i>GOTTA DO SOMETHING,</i>

57
00:03:08,922 --> 00:03:12,190
BEFORE SOMEBODY
GETS HURT, OKAY?

58
00:03:12,259 --> 00:03:14,926
[ Sobs ]
[ Beeps ]

59
00:03:18,598 --> 00:03:20,999
I APPRECIATE-- MISTER?

60
00:03:25,438 --> 00:03:28,740
<i>[ Woman On Police Radio ]</i>
<i>ALL UNITS, HOSTAGE SITUATION</i>
<i>AT SAINT MARY'S HOSPITAL.</i>

61
00:03:28,809 --> 00:03:30,809
<i>MEN CONSIDERED</i>
<i>ARMED AND DANGEROUS.</i>
<i> [ Sirens Wailing ]</i>

62
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:33,845
[ People Clamoring ]

63
00:03:36,617 --> 00:03:38,617
[ Cam ]
BILLY, HURRY UP AND GET
THOSE WINDOWS PAINTED.

64
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:40,619
<i>NOBODY MOVES</i>
<i>AND NOBODY GETS HURT!</i>

65
00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:42,653
<i>WE'RE ALL GONNA BE HERE AWHILE,</i>
<i>SO JUST GET COMFORTABLE.</i>

66
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,656
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>
<i>ALL MEDICAL PERSONNEL.</i>

67
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:48,760
<i>PREPARE TO EVACUATE</i>
<i>ALL NONCRITICAL PATIENTS</i>
<i>FROM THE FIRST FLOOR.</i>

68
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:52,097
HOW YOU DOIN', POP?
[ Machine Beeping ]

69
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:54,566
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>KEEP EVACUATING!</i>

70
00:03:54,634 --> 00:03:57,703
EVERYBODY SIT TIGHT
AND WAIT FOR MY COMMAND.

71
00:03:57,771 --> 00:04:00,305
IF THERE'S A CLEAR SHOT,
YOU LET ME KNOW.

72
00:04:00,373 --> 00:04:03,775
WELL, THAT'S AN INTERESTING
PHILOSOPHY. SHOOT FIRST,
ASK QUESTIONS LATER.

73
00:04:03,844 --> 00:04:07,846
WHO ARE YOU?
SPECIAL AGENT JAROD JACKSON,
CHICAGO F.B.I.

74
00:04:07,915 --> 00:04:10,082
I'M THE HOSTAGE NEGOTIATOR.

75
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:12,217
THIS IS MY SHOW NOW.
DAMN!

76
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,655
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

77
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:18,657
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

78
00:04:18,726 --> 00:04:22,594
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

79
00:04:22,663 --> 00:04:25,764
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

80
00:04:25,832 --> 00:04:29,267
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

81
00:04:29,336 --> 00:04:31,536
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

82
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:34,906
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

83
00:04:34,974 --> 00:04:37,175
- THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.
- PREFERABLY.

84
00:04:37,243 --> 00:04:39,410
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

85
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:41,245
LIFE'S A GIFT.

86
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:54,459
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

87
00:05:00,334 --> 00:05:03,268
BEST WE CAN FIGURE,
THERE'S A HALF A DOZEN
PEOPLE BEING HELD.

88
00:05:03,337 --> 00:05:05,570
INCLUDING THREE PATIENTS IN THE
SEIZED WING THAT COULD DIE...

89
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,638
IN THE NEXT FEW HOURS
WITHOUT TREATMENT.

90
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:10,342
KILL THAT ALARM!
THE HOSTAGE-TAKERS?

91
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:13,778
BILLY LARSEN. HE'S 21.
GOOD KID, WITH NO PRIORS.

92
00:05:13,847 --> 00:05:15,814
BIG BROTHER CAM'S 28.
HE'S A HOTHEAD,

93
00:05:15,882 --> 00:05:17,816
WITH A SHEET THAT GOES
ALL THE WAY BACK TO HIGH SCHOOL.

94
00:05:17,884 --> 00:05:20,752
WEAPONS?
RIFLE AND SHOTGUN,
ACCORDING TO THEIR SISTER.

95
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,854
I'LL NEED HER BROUGHT HERE
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.
YES, SIR.

96
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:28,793
THEY MAKE ANY DEMANDS?
NOTHING YET.

97
00:05:28,862 --> 00:05:31,062
WHAT'S YOUR READ ON
THE SITUATION?
YOU'RE THE BIG BADGE.

98
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:34,499
YOU TELL ME.
THEY'VE ISOLATED
THE SITUATION...

99
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:38,102
TO A SPECIFIC AREA
OF THE HOSPITAL WHERE
THEIR FATHER IS A PATIENT.

100
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:40,772
MY GUESS, IT'S
SOME SORT OF GRIEVANCE
AGAINST THE HOSPITAL.

101
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:44,342
HOW DO YOU FIGURE THAT?
LIKE YOU SAID,
I'M THE BIG BADGE.

102
00:05:44,411 --> 00:05:46,477
LET'S GO TO WORK.

103
00:05:51,384 --> 00:05:54,720
THIS IS F.B.I. SPECIAL AGENT
JAROD JACKSON.

104
00:05:54,788 --> 00:05:57,122
<i>I WANT TO TALK TO YOU</i>
<i>ABOUT YOUR DEMANDS.</i>

105
00:05:58,658 --> 00:06:00,592
IF YOU'VE GOT SOMETHING ON
YOUR MINDS,

106
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:03,461
NOW MIGHT BE
A GOOD TIME TO DISCUSS IT.

107
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,763
THIS IS BETWEEN US
AND THE HOSPITAL.

108
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:07,966
YOU'VE GOT
YOUR FATHER IN THERE.

109
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,268
INNOCENT PEOPLE WHO
NEED MEDICAL ATTENTION.

110
00:06:10,337 --> 00:06:14,038
<i>NEITHER ONE OF US WANT</i>
<i>ANYONE TO DIE HERE TODAY.</i>

111
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:16,040
SO WHY DON'T YOU
TELL ME WHAT YOU WANT,

112
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:20,311
- AND WE CAN END THIS THING.
-<i> [ Cam ] I WANT YOU TO WRITE</i>
<i>  THIS DOWN.</i>

113
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:24,883
<i> $41,342.17.</i>

114
00:06:24,952 --> 00:06:26,918
<i> NOT A PENNY MORE,</i>
<i> NOT A PENNY LESS.</i>

115
00:06:26,987 --> 00:06:28,919
<i> OVER AND OUT.</i>

116
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,924
ALL RIGHT. I'LL SEE
WHAT I CAN DO.

117
00:06:36,029 --> 00:06:38,796
<i>NEED TO ESTABLISH A DIRECT</i>
<i>PHONE LINE INTO THAT ROOM.</i>

118
00:06:38,865 --> 00:06:41,366
YES, SIR.
WHAT IF
THEY DON'T ANSWER?

119
00:06:41,435 --> 00:06:44,635
HELL, THEY COULD HAVE ALREADY
KILLED SOMEBODY, AND WE'D
NEVER KNOW IT.

120
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:48,206
WHERE CAN I GET BLUEPRINTS
OF THIS BUILDING?

121
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:50,708
I CAN GET 'EM HERE
IN 10 MINUTES.
ALL RIGHT.

122
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:54,446
I NEED A FIBER-OPTICS VIDEO
CAMERA, WITH A TRANSMITTER AND
MICROWAVE INTERCEPT.

123
00:06:54,514 --> 00:06:57,115
HOLD ON, EINSTEIN.

124
00:06:57,184 --> 00:07:00,685
THIS TOWN HAS TWO RED LIGHTS,
THREE HARDWARE STORES.

125
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:04,122
MEANING?
MEANING, IF YOU WANT A HAMMER,
I CAN HELP YOU OUT.

126
00:07:04,191 --> 00:07:06,658
YOU WANT TO BUILD A NUCLEAR
REACTOR, YOU'RE OUTTA LUCK.

127
00:07:06,726 --> 00:07:09,961
THIS TOWN HAVE
AN ELECTRONICS STORE?
THAT WE GOT.

128
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,464
I'M GOING TO MAKE A LIST
OF THINGS I NEED.

129
00:07:16,336 --> 00:07:20,338
GET THESE TO ME, A.S.A.P.

130
00:07:20,407 --> 00:07:23,107
[ Engine Revving ]

131
00:07:29,082 --> 00:07:33,651
[ Beeping ]

132
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:47,198
<i>[ Baby Crying ]</i>

133
00:07:47,267 --> 00:07:49,801
<i>[ Crying Continues ]</i>

134
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:11,656
ANGEL.

135
00:08:14,194 --> 00:08:16,327
UGH.
YOU WEREN'T FOLLOWED?

136
00:08:16,396 --> 00:08:20,298
DADDY, YOU LOOK--
OH, I'M SORRY
TO SCARE YOU.

137
00:08:20,366 --> 00:08:22,366
COME ON. COME ON.
COME ON.

138
00:08:22,435 --> 00:08:24,435
DADDY, WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON?
<i>COME ON, COME ON.</i>

139
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:27,171
COME ON BACK HERE.
SIT DOWN.

140
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,875
[ Panting ]
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

141
00:08:29,943 --> 00:08:33,945
UNDERGROUND. THIS IS
THE LAST PLACE THEY'D LOOK.
[ Panting ]

142
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:35,946
NOW, LOOK.

143
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:38,449
THERE'S A STRONGBOX IN SL-22.

144
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,451
IN A PANEL
BEHIND THE FIRE HOSE.
STRONGBOX?

145
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,821
YEAH. IT'S FILLED WITH CASH.
BRING IT TO ME.

146
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:46,958
BUT DON'T TELL ANYBODY.
LIFE AND DEATH, UNDERSTAND?

147
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:50,561
NO, I DON'T.
BRIGITTE AND I HAD TO
LEAVE OUR HIDING PLACE.

148
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:52,864
I NEED THE MONEY
TO LAST US A FEW WEEKS.

149
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:55,867
DADDY, IF I KNEW
WHY YOU WERE RUNNING--
<i> [ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>

150
00:08:57,337 --> 00:08:59,303
[ Beeps ]
WHAT?

151
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:03,207
BAD NEWS. JAROD NEVER SHOWED UP
FOR HIS SHIFT AT THE U.P.S. JOB.

152
00:09:03,276 --> 00:09:06,444
- WE MISSED HIM!
- LYLE?

153
00:09:06,513 --> 00:09:08,479
HE'S LOOKING FOR YOU,
AND HE IS PEEVED.

154
00:09:08,549 --> 00:09:11,616
WHAT ELSE IS NEW?
I WANT YOU TO KEEP
SEARCHING FOR JAROD.

155
00:09:11,684 --> 00:09:13,918
I'LL BE BACK
AS SOON AS I CAN.
[ Kissing Sound ]

156
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:18,790
<i> DADDY?</i>

157
00:09:21,361 --> 00:09:23,494
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>THIS WHOLE THING IS GONNA</i>
<i>TURN INTO A NIGHTMARE.</i>

158
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,496
NOBODY'S GONNA WANT TO
GET TREATED AT THE O.K. CORRAL.

159
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:28,332
WHO ARE YOU?
REBECCA SIMONS,
HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATOR.

160
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,334
DR. STEPHEN FRANKLIN,
CHIEF CARDIOLOGIST.

161
00:09:30,403 --> 00:09:32,536
THEY SPOKE TO THE LARSEN BOYS
BEFORE THEY PULLED THEIR GUNS.

162
00:09:32,605 --> 00:09:34,772
I'M LISTENING.
FAMILY BROUGHT THEIR FATHER.

163
00:09:34,841 --> 00:09:36,841
JAKE LARSEN.
HE WAS COMPLAINING
OF CHEST PAINS.

164
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:39,410
FAMILY THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE
A HEART ATTACK.
HE WAS ADMITTED TO C.C.U.?

165
00:09:39,479 --> 00:09:43,615
YES, YES. I DIAGNOSED HIM
WITH A TYPE OF ARRHYTHMIA
KNOWN AS ATRIAL FIBRILLATION.

166
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:45,617
IT'S PAINFUL, BUT IT'S
NOT LIFE-THREATENING.

167
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:48,420
APPARENTLY, HIS SONS
HAD A DIFFERENT OPINION.
MAYBE I SHOULD HAVE KEPT...

168
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:50,488
MR. LARSEN ONE MORE NIGHT
TO EASE THEIR MINDS.

169
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:52,824
DOES THIS FIGURE MEAN
ANYTHING TO YOU, DOCTOR?

170
00:09:52,892 --> 00:09:56,661
$41,342.17?

171
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,330
- NOT IN PARTICULAR. WHAT IS IT?
- [ Sighs ]
THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

172
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:02,033
<i>[ Simons ] AGENT JACKSON,</i>
<i>THERE ARE PATIENTS IN THERE...</i>

173
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:05,269
<i> WHO WILL DIE</i>
<i> IN THE NEXT FEW HOURS</i>
<i> IF LEFT UNTREATED.</i>

174
00:10:05,338 --> 00:10:08,006
[ Sighs ]
EXCUSE ME.

175
00:10:11,811 --> 00:10:15,013
SARAH, MY NAME IS JAROD.

176
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:18,216
- THE MAN WITH THE TELEPHONE.
- I'M WITH THE F.B.I.

177
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:22,186
I THINK IT'S SAFE TO SAY THAT
NEITHER ONE OF US WOKE UP THIS
MORNING EXPECTING TO BE HERE.

178
00:10:22,255 --> 00:10:25,223
- [ Sighs ]
- I REALIZE THAT
YOU'RE GOING THROUGH...

179
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,126
A VERY DIFFICULT TIME RIGHT NOW.

180
00:10:28,195 --> 00:10:30,828
BUT I HAVE TO UNDERSTAND:
WHY ARE YOUR BROTHERS
DOING THIS?

181
00:10:30,897 --> 00:10:34,032
LOOK, I WANT TO END THIS THING
WITHOUT ANYBODY GETTING HURT.

182
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:36,968
BUT THE TRUTH IS,
I CAN ONLY HOLD THOSE MEN
OFF FOR SO LONG.

183
00:10:37,036 --> 00:10:39,337
<i>MOVE OVER THERE.</i>
<i>GET THAT DOOR.</i>

184
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:46,177
EVERYTHING WAS ALWAYS
PRETTY CRAZY IN OUR FAMILY.

185
00:10:46,246 --> 00:10:50,248
BUT THINGS SEEMED TO REALLY
COME UNDONE AFTER MOM DIED.

186
00:10:50,317 --> 00:10:53,250
ESPECIALLY FOR CAM.
YOUR MOM WAS HERE,
AT THIS HOSPITAL.

187
00:10:54,354 --> 00:10:57,255
SAME ROOM
WHERE DADDY IS.

188
00:10:57,324 --> 00:10:59,290
[ Sighs ]
SHE WAS SO SICK
WHEN THEY SENT HER HOME,

189
00:10:59,359 --> 00:11:03,027
AND... SHE DIED
A FEW DAYS LATER.

190
00:11:03,096 --> 00:11:05,596
AND NOW YOUR FATHER'S HERE.

191
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,465
LOOK, MY BROTHERS MAY BE
DOING THE WRONG THING,

192
00:11:08,534 --> 00:11:10,902
BUT THEY MUST BE DOING IT
FOR THE RIGHT REASON--

193
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:14,372
AND I AM NOT GONNA HELP YOU
KILL THEM FOR IT.

194
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:23,447
AGENT JACKSON.
GOT THE EQUIPMENT YOU WANTED.

195
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:26,984
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S SEE WHAT'S
GOING ON IN THERE.

196
00:11:31,490 --> 00:11:36,127
<i>[ Heart Monitor Beeping ]</i>
<i>[ Moaning ]</i>

197
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,367
<i>WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO, CAM?</i>
I'M THINKING!

198
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:45,803
[ Softly ]
I'M THINKING.

199
00:11:55,382 --> 00:11:58,816
<i>[ Billy ]</i>
<i>I HOPE YOU KNOW WHAT</i>
<i>YOU'RE DOIN', BIG BROTHER.</i>

200
00:12:25,311 --> 00:12:29,380
- I DON'T GET IT.
- SOMETIMES IT HELPS TO BE
A FLY ON THE WALL.

201
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:31,916
OR IN THIS CASE,
THE AIR VENT.

202
00:12:47,733 --> 00:12:50,034
GRAB THOSE BLUEPRINTS.

203
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:02,313
THIS WILL GIVE US A BETTER
SENSE OF THE SPACE WHERE
THE HOSTAGES ARE BEING HELD,

204
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:04,949
WINDOWS, EXITS--

205
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:09,854
<i>[ Deputy ]</i>
<i>I'LL BE DAMNED.</i>

206
00:13:30,043 --> 00:13:34,345
I COULD USE THIS TO GET A CLEAN
SHOT. I HAVE MEN ON THE ROOF,
NEXT TO THE SEIZED WING.

207
00:13:34,414 --> 00:13:37,181
<i>ISN'T IT YOUR JOB TO CONSIDER</i>
<i>EVERYBODY'S SAFETY?</i>

208
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:40,751
MY JOB IS TO SAVE THE LIVES
OF THOSE<i> CIVILIANS</i> INSIDE!

209
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:44,388
<i>IF I HESITATE, AND ONE</i>
<i>INNOCENT PERSON DIES,</i>
<i>IT'S MY FAULT.</i>

210
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:47,859
I WON'T MAKE THAT MISTAKE.

211
00:13:55,935 --> 00:13:58,937
THE SHERIFF SEEMS
A LITTLE ON EDGE.

212
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:01,572
<i>[ Deputy ]</i>
<i>HE HAS HIS REASONS.</i>

213
00:14:01,641 --> 00:14:04,274
<i> [ Jake ]</i>
<i> CAM! WHAT THE HELL DO YOU</i>
<i> THINK YOU'RE DOIN'?</i>

214
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:07,111
- [ Cam ]
I KNOW WHAT I'M DOIN', POP.
-<i> YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE...</i>

215
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:09,581
IF YOUR MAMA WAS STILL ALIVE.

216
00:14:12,118 --> 00:14:16,554
<i>WELL, SHE'S NOT, AND I AM.</i>
<i>STOP TALKIN'.</i>

217
00:14:16,622 --> 00:14:20,357
JUST GET SOME REST.

218
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:23,561
<i>MAN, THERE ARE GUNS AND BADGES</i>
<i>ALL OVER THE PLACE DOWN THERE.</i>

219
00:14:23,629 --> 00:14:26,397
[ Sighs ]
WELL, WHAT THE HELL DID
YOU THINK WAS GONNA HAPPEN?

220
00:14:26,466 --> 00:14:28,733
COME IN HERE WITH GUNS,
THEY'D LEAVE A PARKING TICKET
ON OUR CAR?

221
00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:32,570
JUST KEEP LOOKOUT.

222
00:14:34,273 --> 00:14:37,641
SHERIFF SAYS, KILL
THE AIR AND THE LIGHTS.

223
00:14:39,512 --> 00:14:41,646
<i>[ Motors Decelerating ]</i>

224
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:44,815
YOU TWO GET DOWN!

225
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,918
-<i> [ Jake Gasping ]</i>
- WHAT NOW?

226
00:14:54,661 --> 00:14:57,395
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

227
00:14:57,464 --> 00:14:59,830
- YEAH.
- CAM. THIS IS AGENT JACKSON.

228
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,933
TURN THE LIGHTS
AND AIR BACK ON!

229
00:15:02,001 --> 00:15:05,436
ALL RIGHT, I'LL GIVE YOU
WHAT YOU WANT, AND YOU GIVE ME
A COUPLE OF HOSTAGES.

230
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,309
WHY SHOULD I TRUST YOU?
<i>YOU HAVE MY WORD.</i>

231
00:15:11,378 --> 00:15:14,946
NO HARM WILL COME
TO YOU OR YOUR BROTHER,
AS LONG AS WE KEEP TALKING.

232
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:20,685
IT'S GOING TO GET
REALLY WARM IN THERE.
NOW, DO WE HAVE A DEAL?

233
00:15:22,388 --> 00:15:25,623
<i>CAM. YOU CAN TRUST ME.</i>

234
00:15:29,863 --> 00:15:32,430
<i>CAM? TALK TO ME.</i>
<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>

235
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:36,500
GET DOWN!
EVERYBODY GET DOWN!

236
00:15:36,569 --> 00:15:39,603
[ Screaming ]

237
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:41,872
<i>[ Gunshots Continue ]</i>

238
00:15:50,317 --> 00:15:52,817
<i>I HAD CAM'S TRUST UNTIL</i>
<i>YOUR SNIPER GOT TRIGGER-HAPPY.</i>

239
00:15:52,886 --> 00:15:56,888
HEY! CAM LARSEN ISN'T
A MAN WHO CAN BE TRUSTED.

240
00:15:56,957 --> 00:15:59,891
HE INCITED A RIOT
WHILE HE WAS IN PRISON.
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

241
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:03,227
THE GUARDS WERE BEATING
THE PRISONERS, AND THEY WERE
CONVICTED ON BRUTALITY CHARGES.

242
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:05,229
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

243
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:08,366
I GOT CAM ON THE LINE.

244
00:16:10,537 --> 00:16:12,236
CAM.
ARE YOU GUYS CRAZY?

245
00:16:12,305 --> 00:16:14,305
I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH THAT
SHOOTING, I SWEAR TO YOU.

246
00:16:14,374 --> 00:16:17,208
LOOK, I-IT'S IMPORTANT
THAT I COME IN THERE AND
SPEAK TO YOU FACE-TO-FACE.

247
00:16:17,277 --> 00:16:19,410
<i>I'M NOT HERE TO TALK!</i>
<i> I'M HERE TO SAVE MY DAD'S LIFE.</i>

248
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:23,214
UNDERSTAND?
IT'S TOO HOT IN HERE.
TURN ON THE AIR, NOW.

249
00:16:23,283 --> 00:16:26,918
YES. YES, I WILL TURN
THE AIR CONDITIONING
BACK ON, I PROMISE.

250
00:16:26,987 --> 00:16:29,854
NOW, CAN I COME IN THERE?
[ Sighs Deeply ]

251
00:16:29,923 --> 00:16:33,124
OKAY. BUT JUST YOU.
UNARMED. TEN MINUTES.

252
00:16:33,193 --> 00:16:36,394
ALL RIGHT. TEN MINUTES.
[ Line Clicks ]

253
00:16:36,463 --> 00:16:39,564
THOSE ARE CAM'S KIDS.
I HAD THEM BROUGHT IN.

254
00:16:39,632 --> 00:16:43,034
TO GET UNDER HIS SKIN?
TO GET
INTO HIS HEART.

255
00:17:10,129 --> 00:17:14,265
<i>[ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>
WHAT?

256
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:17,635
- WHERE ARE YOU?
- NEVER MIND.
DID YOU FIND JAROD?

257
00:17:17,704 --> 00:17:19,737
I WAS SCANNING POLICE CHATTER
IN FLETCHER RIDGE,

258
00:17:19,806 --> 00:17:22,807
AND I CAME ACROSS A HOSTAGE
NEGOTIATION SITUATION THERE
AT A HOSPITAL.

259
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:25,209
F.B.I. INVOLVEMENT.
AND?

260
00:17:25,278 --> 00:17:27,211
IT SOUNDED LIKE SOMETHING
THAT JAROD WOULD BE DRAWN TO,

261
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:29,947
SO I-I CONTACTED THE CHICAGO
OFFICE OF THE F.B.I.--
LET ME GUESS.

262
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:33,250
NO F.B.I. INVOLVEMENT.
IF THERE WERE ANY AGENTS
ON THE JOB THERE,

263
00:17:33,319 --> 00:17:38,556
THEY WOULD HAVE COME
FROM THE CHICAGO OFFICE,
AND THEY HADN'T SENT ANYBODY.

264
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:41,959
[ Groans ] HE NEVER LEFT TOWN.
GET THE JET READY, AND I'LL
BE BACK AS SOON AS I CAN.

265
00:17:45,332 --> 00:17:47,265
- [ Softly ] WHAT ABOUT LYLE?
- LYLE WHO?

266
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,433
[ Hangs Up Receiver, Beeps ]

267
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,577
HMM.

268
00:17:59,645 --> 00:18:02,480
I LOVE ICE CREAM.
[ Smacking Lips ]

269
00:18:04,451 --> 00:18:08,586
I WANT TO HELP YOUR DAD,
BUT I'M GOING TO NEED
YOUR HELP TO DO IT.

270
00:18:08,655 --> 00:18:11,823
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

271
00:18:11,892 --> 00:18:15,960
<i>LAST NIGHT, DADDY WAS</i>
<i>YELLING AT BILLY AND SARAH.</i>

272
00:18:16,028 --> 00:18:20,765
- HE WAS ANGRY?
- HE SAID THE HOSPITAL WAS GONNA
SEND GRANDPA JAKE HOME TO DIE.

273
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:24,102
JUST LIKE THEY DID GRANDMA.
HE SAID THEY WERE MURDERERS.

274
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:28,873
- MURDERERS.
- [ Sighs ]

275
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:32,043
- LOOKS LIKE YOU
JUST LOST A TOOTH.
- IT FELL OUT.

276
00:18:32,112 --> 00:18:35,013
ARE YOU GOING TO
PUT IT UNDER YOUR PILLOW?
FOR THE TOOTH FAIRY?

277
00:18:35,081 --> 00:18:36,881
TONIGHT.
<i>WOW.</i>

278
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:39,650
HOW MUCH YOU FIGURE
YOU'RE GONNA GET?
<i> MM--</i>

279
00:18:39,719 --> 00:18:41,852
MAYBE A DOLLAR.
<i>A DOLLAR.</i>

280
00:18:41,921 --> 00:18:44,456
HOW WOULD YOU...

281
00:18:45,725 --> 00:18:47,992
<i>[ Helicopter Whirring ]</i>
LIKE TO MAKE FIVE?

282
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:50,194
<i>[ Helicopter Passing By ]</i>

283
00:18:52,099 --> 00:18:55,399
<i>IT'S AGENT JACKSON.</i>
<i>I'M COMING IN, AND I'M UNARMED.</i>

284
00:18:55,468 --> 00:18:58,369
<i>[ Heart Monitor Beeping ]</i>

285
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:01,038
CHECK HIM OUT.

286
00:19:05,879 --> 00:19:08,713
HE'S CLEAN.

287
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:16,387
<i> COULD HAVE GOT</i>
<i> SOMEBODY KILLED,</i>
<i> SHOOTIN' IN HERE LIKE THAT.</i>

288
00:19:16,455 --> 00:19:19,356
THAT WAS A MISTAKE.
THAT OFFICER HAS BEEN
REMOVED FROM THE LINE.

289
00:19:19,425 --> 00:19:22,426
WE'RE NOT EXACTLY TALKING ABOUT
AN ELITE POLICE FORCE OUT THERE.

290
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:25,330
-<i> [ Cam ] TELL ME ABOUT IT.</i>
- SO, ARE YOU READY
TO END THIS THING, CAM?

291
00:19:25,398 --> 00:19:28,099
<i>GET YOUR FATHER TAKEN CARE OF?</i>

292
00:19:28,168 --> 00:19:30,735
<i>I KNOW YOU CARE ABOUT HIM.</i>
<i>THAT'S WHY YOU'RE DOING THIS.</i>

293
00:19:30,803 --> 00:19:36,541
- YOU DON'T KNOW NOTHIN'.
- WHY DON'T YOU EXPLAIN IT
TO ME?

294
00:19:36,610 --> 00:19:40,478
$41,342.17.

295
00:19:40,547 --> 00:19:44,214
-THAT'S AN ODD PRICE
TO PLACE ON SOMEBODY'S LIFE.
-IT'S NOT MY PRICE. IT'S THEIRS.

296
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:48,753
-<i> [ Moaning ]</i>
- OH, SHE'S GETTIN' WORSE.

297
00:19:48,822 --> 00:19:50,855
- HEY-HEY!
- SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

298
00:19:50,924 --> 00:19:54,358
YOU GONNA KEEP HER HERE
AND LET HER DIE? HER LIFE
FOR YOUR FATHER'S, IS THAT IT?

299
00:19:54,427 --> 00:19:56,460
- CAM, MAYBE WE SHOULD
LET HER GO, HUH?
- BILLY, SHUT UP!

300
00:19:56,529 --> 00:19:58,596
- [ Gasps ]
-<i> YOU'RE NOT A KILLER, CAM.</i>

301
00:19:58,664 --> 00:20:01,965
YOU LET THIS WOMAN DIE,
AND YOU'RE GOING TO SPEND
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE IN PRISON.

302
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,535
YOU AND BILLY, HERE.

303
00:20:06,672 --> 00:20:10,608
- THINK ABOUT YOUR CHILDREN.
- MY KIDS.

304
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:16,647
- THEY WON'T UNDERSTAND THIS.
- CAN'T BELIEVE HOW MUCH YOUR
LITTLE BOY LOOKS LIKE YOU.

305
00:20:16,716 --> 00:20:19,383
YOU TALKED TO MY BOY?
<i> IT'S PROCEDURE.</i>
<i> OH, CODY.</i>

306
00:20:19,452 --> 00:20:21,485
HE ASKED ME
TO GIVE YOU THIS.

307
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:31,262
<i>[ Helicopter Whirring ]</i>

308
00:20:36,803 --> 00:20:40,170
- SO, HOW MUCH DO YOU WANT ME
TO LEAVE FOR HIM?
- HOW MUCH?

309
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,640
MONEY. FROM THE TOOTH FAIRY.

310
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:46,343
RIGHT. TOOTH FAIRY.

311
00:20:46,412 --> 00:20:49,180
YOU GOT A DOLLAR?

312
00:20:49,249 --> 00:20:51,515
- ALL I GOT'S A FIVE.
- GIVE IT HERE.

313
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,985
- YOU'RE GONNA GIVE HIM
FIVE BUCKS FOR A BABY TOOTH?
- JUST GIVE ME THE MONEY.

314
00:20:57,891 --> 00:21:01,792
YOU WALK OUTTA HERE NOW, YOU
CAN STILL PUT THIS MONEY UNDER
YOUR SON'S PILLOW YOURSELF.

315
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:06,063
<i> I CAN'T LEAVE HIM.</i>
<i> [ Sighs ]</i>

316
00:21:06,132 --> 00:21:08,432
MAN, YOU DON'T GET IT, DO YOU?

317
00:21:08,501 --> 00:21:12,270
<i>THIS ISN'T JUST ABOUT MY FATHER.</i>
<i>IT'S ABOUT EVERY PERSON</i>
<i>OUT THERE WHO IS SICK...</i>

318
00:21:12,339 --> 00:21:14,538
AND DESERVES TO BE
TREATED WITH DIGNITY.

319
00:21:18,444 --> 00:21:22,012
THEY'RE GONNA SEND THIS MAN
HOME. DOES HE LOOK LIKE
HE SHOULD GO HOME TO YOU?

320
00:21:22,081 --> 00:21:25,282
- [ Gasping ]
- AT LEAST, GIVE ME A HOSTAGE.

321
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:27,318
[ Scoffs ]
<i> YOU GOTTA WORK</i>
<i> WITH ME HERE, CAM.</i>

322
00:21:27,387 --> 00:21:30,020
THERE ARE A LOT OF PEOPLE
OUT THERE LOOKING FOR ANY
REASON TO SHOOT YOU...

323
00:21:30,089 --> 00:21:32,156
<i> AND YOUR LITTLE BROTHER</i>
<i> OVER HERE.</i>

324
00:21:35,561 --> 00:21:39,163
<i>[ Woman Breathing With</i>
<i>  Difficulty, Coughing ]</i>

325
00:21:39,232 --> 00:21:42,333
<i>ALL RIGHT. TAKE THAT LADY.</i>
<i>TAKE HER. HELP HIM.</i>

326
00:21:42,402 --> 00:21:44,735
<i> UNHOOK HER,</i>
<i> AND GET HER OUT OF HERE.</i>

327
00:21:44,804 --> 00:21:47,070
- WHAT ABOUT THE OTHERS?
- ONE AT A TIME.

328
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:50,174
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
ONE AT A TIME.

329
00:21:51,544 --> 00:21:54,011
<i> YOU'RE DOING A GOOD THING</i>
<i> HERE, CAM.</i>

330
00:22:02,455 --> 00:22:05,656
<i>[ Chattering On Police Radio ]</i>

331
00:22:05,725 --> 00:22:09,360
<i>IF SOME OF THOSE PATIENTS</i>
<i>DON'T GET TREATMENT REAL SOON,</i>
<i>WE COULD HAVE A DISASTER HERE.</i>

332
00:22:11,431 --> 00:22:14,065
MEANING?
MANEUVER CAM TO A WINDOW.

333
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:16,066
ONE SHOT,
AND IT'S OVER.

334
00:22:16,135 --> 00:22:18,703
WHY IS IT THAT YOU FEEL THAT
BULLETS ARE THE ONLY OPTION?

335
00:22:18,771 --> 00:22:22,106
ONE SHOT.

336
00:22:25,445 --> 00:22:29,013
DEPUTY, MAY I HAVE
A WORD WITH YOU?

337
00:22:30,317 --> 00:22:34,418
[ Heart Monitor Beeping ]

338
00:22:34,487 --> 00:22:36,420
[ Spitting ]

339
00:22:38,491 --> 00:22:42,960
- WHAT'S YOUR NAME?
- LINDSAY.

340
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:45,329
L-LINDSAY TYLER.

341
00:22:48,168 --> 00:22:50,701
SHOULDN'T BITE YOUR NAILS,
LINDSAY. IT'S A BAD HABIT.

342
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:55,639
- I KNOW.
- Y-YOU DON'T REMEMBER ME,
DO YOU?

343
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:58,643
- SHOULD I?
- CINDY PERKINS?

344
00:22:58,711 --> 00:23:01,612
JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL,
SADIE HAWKINS DANCE--

345
00:23:01,681 --> 00:23:03,915
I ASKED YOU TO DANCE ONCE,
AND YOU SAID YES?

346
00:23:03,983 --> 00:23:08,218
- [ Sighs ]
- I HAD STRINGY HAIR, BRACES--

347
00:23:09,655 --> 00:23:11,655
YEAH, YEAH.

348
00:23:15,695 --> 00:23:20,097
YOU CHASED ME AROUND THE GYM
ALL NIGHT. WHAT WAS THAT,
10, 15 YEARS AGO?

349
00:23:20,166 --> 00:23:23,234
YOU KEPT ASKING THE BAND
TO PLAY YOUR FAVORITE SONG.

350
00:23:23,303 --> 00:23:26,270
- "DREAM WEAVER." [ Chuckles ]
- THAT'S A DAMN FINE SONG.

351
00:23:26,339 --> 00:23:28,939
<i>[ Helicopter Passing Overhead ]</i>

352
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:35,112
YOU KNOW, MY DAD
DIED OF HEART PROBLEMS.

353
00:23:35,181 --> 00:23:37,681
<i>TH-THAT'S WHY</i>
<i>I WENT INTO NURSING.</i>

354
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:40,450
YOUR FATHER SORT OF
REMINDS ME OF MY DAD.

355
00:23:40,519 --> 00:23:44,021
<i>[ Jake Coughing ]</i>

356
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:48,025
LOOK, CINDY--
[ Sighs Deeply ]

357
00:23:48,094 --> 00:23:50,827
I'M SORRY ABOUT ALL THIS.
I NEVER MEANT TO--

358
00:23:50,896 --> 00:23:52,897
- CAM?
- [ Alarm Beeping ]

359
00:23:52,966 --> 00:23:55,165
<i> CAM, COME HERE.</i>
GO, GO, GO, GO,
GO, GO, GO.

360
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,871
HE'S NOT BREATHING!

361
00:23:59,939 --> 00:24:02,807
- [ Ringing ]
- I NEED A DOCTOR IN HERE NOW!
NOW!

362
00:24:02,876 --> 00:24:05,343
<i> ALL RIGHT, CAM.</i>
<i> I'LL SEND ONE IN.</i>
<i> GET YOUR GEAR.</i>

363
00:24:05,411 --> 00:24:08,179
-<i> [ Doctor ] NO.</i>
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

364
00:24:08,247 --> 00:24:11,182
<i>THOSE MEN ARE HEAVILY ARMED,</i>
<i>AND THEY'VE THREATENED THE LIVES</i>
<i>OF INNOCENT PEOPLE.</i>

365
00:24:11,251 --> 00:24:14,152
<i> UNLESS YOU CAN</i>
<i> ASSURE ME OF MY SAFETY,</i>
<i> I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.</i>

366
00:24:18,691 --> 00:24:21,491
GET THE LIGHTS BACK ON
IN THAT ROOM.
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

367
00:24:21,561 --> 00:24:23,794
<i>AGENT JACKSON.</i>
<i> AGENT JACKSON!</i>

368
00:24:28,267 --> 00:24:31,235
CAM, IT'S AGENT JACKSON.
I'M COMING IN.

369
00:24:31,304 --> 00:24:34,205
- I ASKED FOR A DOCTOR!
- CAM, HE'S GOING INTO
CARDIAC ARREST!

370
00:24:34,274 --> 00:24:36,173
- LET HIM IN, CAM.
-<i> [ Alarm Buzzing ]</i>

371
00:24:36,242 --> 00:24:39,243
WE DIDN'T COME HERE
TO KILL OUR OWN FATHER.
<i>[ Alarm Continues ]</i>

372
00:24:40,813 --> 00:24:44,515
- [ Assisted Breathing ]
- COME IN!

373
00:24:46,086 --> 00:24:47,718
EASY, EASY!
WHERE IS THE DOCTOR?

374
00:24:47,787 --> 00:24:50,054
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>THERE ISN'T A DOCTOR AVAILABLE.</i>
<i>I CAN HANDLE THIS.</i>

375
00:24:50,123 --> 00:24:53,224
- [ Exhales ]
- [ Huffs ]

376
00:24:55,761 --> 00:24:59,997
<i>I HOPE YOU CAN HANDLE THIS.</i>
<i>'CAUSE IF MY OLD MAN DIES,</i>
<i>SO DO YOU.</i>

377
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:04,167
[ One Long Beep ]

378
00:25:10,777 --> 00:25:14,111
-<i> [ Cindy ]</i>
<i>  HE'S BEEN FLAT FOR 15 SECONDS.</i>
- [ Electrical Whining ]

379
00:25:16,215 --> 00:25:18,315
- PADDLES CHARGED?
- CLEAR.

380
00:25:18,384 --> 00:25:20,818
- [ Electrical Thumping ]
-<i> [ Cindy ] NOTHING. 25 SECONDS.</i>

381
00:25:20,886 --> 00:25:22,219
- TALK TO HIM.
- WHAT?

382
00:25:22,287 --> 00:25:24,354
I NEED HIM TO FIGHT.
TELL HIM A STORY
FROM YOUR PAST.

383
00:25:24,423 --> 00:25:26,557
<i> SOMETHING YOU DID TOGETHER.</i>
<i> TALK TO HIM. CLEAR.</i>

384
00:25:26,626 --> 00:25:28,325
[ Thumps ]
NOTHING.

385
00:25:28,394 --> 00:25:30,361
-<i> WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.</i>
<i>  TALK TO HIM.</i>
-<i> [ Cindy ] 40 SECONDS.</i>

386
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:34,064
DAD, REMEMBER WHEN I WAS
FIVE YEARS OLD,

387
00:25:34,133 --> 00:25:36,333
HOW YOU USED TO TAKE ME
HUNTING UP NEAR PATCHETT LAKE?

388
00:25:36,402 --> 00:25:38,502
I'M GOING TO 360 JOULES.
KEEP TALKING.

389
00:25:38,571 --> 00:25:40,972
<i> [ Paddles Charging ]</i>
USED TO WAKE ME UP EARLY,
WHILE IT WAS STILL DARK OUT.

390
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,906
<i>I USED TO HATE GETTIN' UP</i>
<i>SO EARLY, BUT YOU SAID</i>
<i>IT WAS IMPORTANT...</i>

391
00:25:42,975 --> 00:25:44,808
-<i> TO GET OUT BEFORE THE SUN.</i>
-<i> [ Jarod ] CLEAR!</i>

392
00:25:47,747 --> 00:25:51,915
YOU TOLD ME THAT A SUNRISE
IN THE WOODS WAS AS CLOSE TO GOD
AS A BREATHIN' MAN COULD GET.

393
00:25:51,984 --> 00:25:54,484
<i>[ Paddles Whining ]</i>
<i>REMEMBER WHEN YOU SAID THAT?</i>
<i> REMEMBER THAT, DAD?</i>

394
00:25:54,553 --> 00:25:56,587
-<i> [ Cindy ] ONE MINUTE.</i>
- CLEAR.

395
00:25:56,656 --> 00:25:58,755
- [ Thumping ]
- [ Gasping ]

396
00:25:58,824 --> 00:26:03,026
COME ON, OLD MAN. FIGHT!
DON'T GIVE UP! FIGHT.
<i> [ Cindy ] 70 SECONDS.</i>

397
00:26:03,095 --> 00:26:05,396
-<i> DON'T LEAVE US, PLEASE.</i>
-<i> [ Paddles Charging ]</i>

398
00:26:05,464 --> 00:26:07,998
-<i> WE NEED YOU.</i>
- I'M GONNA HIT HIM AGAIN.
CLEAR!

399
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,234
COME ON,
YOU CAN FIGHT THIS!
COME ON, POP.

400
00:26:10,303 --> 00:26:13,737
WE NEED YOU.
CODY AND KERRY
NEED THEIR GRANDPA.

401
00:26:13,806 --> 00:26:16,340
<i> IF WE DON'T GET HIM BACK</i>
<i> QUICK, THERE COULD BE</i>
<i> PERMANENT DAMAGE.</i>

402
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:19,776
DON'T DIE ON ME, DAD.
HANG IN THERE. COME ON.
DON'T DIE ON ME, DAD.

403
00:26:19,845 --> 00:26:22,213
-<i> COME ON, POP!</i>
- I'M GETTING A PULSE.

404
00:26:22,282 --> 00:26:25,383
<i>[ Steady Beeping ]</i>

405
00:26:26,953 --> 00:26:29,753
THEY REALLY TRAIN 'EM
UP THERE AT THE F.B.I. ACADEMY.

406
00:26:29,822 --> 00:26:32,523
<i>[ Police Chattering</i>
<i>  On Radio ]</i>

407
00:26:32,592 --> 00:26:35,793
LET'S GET A CLOSER LOOK.

408
00:26:47,006 --> 00:26:48,939
[ Whirring, Banging ]

409
00:26:50,976 --> 00:26:54,244
- WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?
- WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

410
00:26:54,313 --> 00:26:57,881
- I DON'T KNOW.
THE SIGNAL WENT DEAD.
- [ Panting ] LOOK, CAM.

411
00:26:57,950 --> 00:27:01,585
<i>YOU'VE MADE ALL THE RIGHT</i>
<i>CHOICES UP TILL NOW. LET ME TAKE</i>
<i>ANOTHER HOSTAGE OUT OF HERE.</i>

412
00:27:06,159 --> 00:27:09,893
- OKAY. YEAH. YOU, CINDY.
GO HOME.
- NO.

413
00:27:09,962 --> 00:27:11,928
- WHAT?
- I DON'T LEAVE UNTIL YOU DO.

414
00:27:13,032 --> 00:27:15,332
FOR<i> MY</i> FATHER.

415
00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:21,972
I-I'LL GO.

416
00:27:24,176 --> 00:27:26,643
-<i> I'VE GOT TO GET</i>
<i>  THAT PICTURE BACK.</i>
-<i> [ Jarod, Indistinct ]</i>

417
00:27:26,712 --> 00:27:29,679
-<i> [ Deputy ] WE'VE STILL</i>
<i>  GOT SOUND, SHERIFF.</i>
- [ Whirring, Banging ]

418
00:27:41,527 --> 00:27:44,228
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

419
00:27:45,331 --> 00:27:47,865
YOU'VE BEEN WATCHIN' US
THE WHOLE TIME!

420
00:27:47,934 --> 00:27:52,336
I SHOULD BLOW YOU AWAY
RIGHT NOW! I KNEW I COULDN'T
TRUST YOU PEOPLE!

421
00:27:55,575 --> 00:27:57,842
- [ Moaning ]
- NO, NO!

422
00:27:57,910 --> 00:28:02,213
NO. CAM. NOT LIKE THIS.

423
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:05,148
<i>[ Helicopter Whirring ]</i>

424
00:28:09,655 --> 00:28:12,089
ALL RIGHT. GET OUT.

425
00:28:12,157 --> 00:28:15,392
TAKE HER WITH YOU.
NO MORE TALKING!
JUST GET OUT!

426
00:28:25,638 --> 00:28:27,571
YOU ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

427
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,040
PLEASE TAKE CARE OF HER.

428
00:28:33,011 --> 00:28:35,579
- ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?
- HEY, IT WAS AN ACCIDENT!

429
00:28:35,648 --> 00:28:38,315
YOU COULD HAVE GOTTEN
ALL OF US KILLED IN THERE.
WE CAN'T KEEP PUSHING HIM.

430
00:28:38,384 --> 00:28:42,352
WHY CAN'T YOU GET THAT
THROUGH YOUR HEAD?
I'VE HAD A BELLYFUL OF YOU.

431
00:28:42,421 --> 00:28:46,190
OH, YEAH? AND WHAT
IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?
YOU'RE THE BIG BADGE.

432
00:28:46,259 --> 00:28:48,759
YOU FIGURE IT OUT.

433
00:28:50,396 --> 00:28:52,996
<i> [ Keypad Beeping ]</i>

434
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:56,667
[ Line Ringing, Clicking ]
ALICE? GET ME THE NUMBER FOR
THE F.B.I. OFFICE IN CHICAGO.

435
00:28:57,737 --> 00:28:59,736
[ Sighs ]

436
00:28:59,805 --> 00:29:03,173
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>I DOUBT YOU'LL FIND MISS PARKER</i>
<i>SEARCHING THROUGH HER DESK.</i>

437
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:08,044
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>WE SAW HER THIS MORNING. I THINK</i>
<i>SHE HAD SOME ERRANDS TO RUN.</i>

438
00:29:08,113 --> 00:29:10,514
SHE DIDN'T SAY
WHERE SHE WAS GOING?

439
00:29:10,583 --> 00:29:14,117
YOU KNOW YOUR SISTER.
YOU KNOW SHE DANCES TO THE BEAT
OF A DIFFERENT DRUMMER.

440
00:29:14,186 --> 00:29:16,954
<i>[ Slams Book Closed ]</i>
SO I'VE NOTICED.

441
00:29:19,292 --> 00:29:21,258
YOU TWO WOULDN'T LIE
TO ME, WOULD YOU?

442
00:29:24,597 --> 00:29:28,098
<i> SO, A-ANYBODY SEE</i>
<i> THE, UH, REDSKINS GAME</i>
<i> THIS WEEKEND?</i>

443
00:30:10,743 --> 00:30:14,744
<i> AGENT JACKSON. ANY IDEA</i>
<i> WHEN I MIGHT BE ALLOWED</i>
<i> BACK IN MY OFFICE?</i>

444
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:17,414
- NO IDEA.
- OH. [ Sighs ]

445
00:30:19,885 --> 00:30:22,453
THAT'S VERY IMPRESSIVE,
THE WAY YOU HANDLED
THAT CODE SITUATION.

446
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:25,322
I DIDN'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHOICE, DID I?

447
00:30:27,927 --> 00:30:29,959
TELL ME SOMETHING.

448
00:30:30,028 --> 00:30:33,330
HOW ARE INSURANCE CLAIMS
PROCESSED AT THIS HOSPITAL?

449
00:30:33,399 --> 00:30:37,501
IN THE MIDDLE OF A HOSTAGE
SITUATION, AND YOU'RE WONDERING
ABOUT BILLING PROCEDURE?

450
00:30:37,569 --> 00:30:41,138
I'M JUST CURIOUS.
FOR INSTANCE, AN H.M.O. CLAIM.

451
00:30:41,206 --> 00:30:44,041
H.M.O.'s RELY ON
THE INFORMATION PROVIDED
BY THE ATTENDING PHYSICIAN.

452
00:30:44,110 --> 00:30:47,644
<i> SO A PARTICULAR</i>
<i> MEDICAL PROCEDURE WOULD</i>
<i> BE APPROVED OR DENIED...</i>

453
00:30:47,713 --> 00:30:49,813
BASED UPON YOUR RECOMMENDATION.
<i> YEAH, THAT.</i>

454
00:30:49,882 --> 00:30:52,516
AND THE RECOMMENDATION OF
THE FACILITIES ADMINISTRATOR.

455
00:30:52,585 --> 00:30:55,118
- REBECCA SIMONS.
- IN THE CASE OF
THIS HOSPITAL, YES.

456
00:30:55,187 --> 00:30:59,022
<i> WHAT PERCENTAGE OF</i>
<i> MAJOR SURGERIES HAVE BEEN</i>
<i> DENIED AT THIS HOSPITAL?</i>

457
00:30:59,091 --> 00:31:01,558
- [ Sighs ]
OH, I-I DON'T KNOW.
- TAKE A GUESS.

458
00:31:01,627 --> 00:31:03,460
[ Stammering ]
I-I DON'T KNOW.
FIFTY PERCENT?

459
00:31:03,529 --> 00:31:07,630
SIXTY-EIGHT PERCENT:
11 PERCENTAGE POINTS HIGHER
THAN THE NATIONAL AVERAGE.

460
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:12,836
- WHY DO YOU THINK THAT IS?
- MAYBE THERE ARE JUST A LOT OF
HEALTHY PEOPLE IN THIS TOWN.

461
00:31:15,207 --> 00:31:18,141
MAYBE.
<i> [ Helicopter Whirring ]</i>

462
00:31:23,949 --> 00:31:26,684
[ Dialing Phone ]

463
00:31:26,752 --> 00:31:29,486
[ Line Clicking ]
UH, WE NEED TO TALK.

464
00:31:29,555 --> 00:31:32,689
<i> [ Siren Wailing ]</i>

465
00:31:32,758 --> 00:31:35,491
[ Scoffs ]
YOU LOOK LIKE HELL.

466
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:40,096
[ Chuckling ]
THAT'S THE WAY IT IS
WHEN YOU'RE DYIN'.

467
00:31:44,070 --> 00:31:46,203
GOT YOURSELF IN
A REAL MESS HERE, BOY.

468
00:31:46,272 --> 00:31:49,239
LIKE EVERYTHING ELSE
IN MY LIFE.

469
00:31:49,308 --> 00:31:54,878
LOOK, MAYBE I DIDN'T DO
THE THINGS I SHOULD HAVE
WHEN YOU WERE SMALL.

470
00:31:54,946 --> 00:31:58,915
<i> HELL, I--</i>
<i> I WAS MAKIN' IT UP</i>
<i> AS I WENT.</i>

471
00:31:58,985 --> 00:32:04,254
<i> BUT I TAUGHT YOU KIDS</i>
<i> RIGHT FROM WRONG.</i>
<i> I DID THAT.</i>

472
00:32:04,323 --> 00:32:06,557
- I'M TRYIN' TO SAVE YOU, DAD.
- WHY?

473
00:32:06,625 --> 00:32:09,593
BECAUSE WE'RE A FAMILY.

474
00:32:09,661 --> 00:32:12,696
I NEVER KNEW
MY OWN OLD MAN.

475
00:32:12,764 --> 00:32:15,398
NOT MORE THAN
A SMACK IN THE HEAD
NOW AND THEN.

476
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:19,702
I JUST DID THE BEST
THAT I COULD, AND--

477
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:24,007
<i> [ Sobs ]</i>
<i> WHEN YOUR MAMA DIED--</i>

478
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:26,777
I THINK A LITTLE BIT
OF ME WENT TOO.

479
00:32:26,845 --> 00:32:29,947
GUESS WE'VE BEEN FIGHTIN'
THE SAME PAIN.

480
00:32:30,015 --> 00:32:33,984
[ Sobbing ]
I MISS HER. EVERY DAY.

481
00:32:35,854 --> 00:32:38,221
ME TOO, POP.
[ Exhales ]

482
00:32:42,895 --> 00:32:46,596
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>$41,342.17.</i>

483
00:32:46,665 --> 00:32:50,300
THIS IS THE EXACT
AMOUNT THIS HOSPITAL CHARGES
FOR HEART BYPASS SURGERY.

484
00:32:50,368 --> 00:32:54,705
WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?
JAKE LARSEN HAS SKY-HIGH LEVELS
OF CREATINE KINASE ENZYME...

485
00:32:54,773 --> 00:32:56,707
IN HIS BLOOD.
SO?

486
00:32:56,775 --> 00:33:00,610
HIS FINGERTIPS ARE BLUE
FROM LACK OF OXYGEN.
I STILL DON'T FOLLOW.

487
00:33:00,679 --> 00:33:03,313
HE HAS HEART DISEASE.
HE'S HEADED FOR
A MASSIVE HEART ATTACK.

488
00:33:03,381 --> 00:33:06,183
HIS ONLY CHANCE OF SURVIVAL
IS HEART BYPASS SURGERY.

489
00:33:06,251 --> 00:33:09,519
THE SAME SURGERY
THIS HOSPITAL DENIED HIM.
[ Sighs ]

490
00:33:11,256 --> 00:33:14,858
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?
EXCUSE ME?

491
00:33:14,927 --> 00:33:19,029
I CALLED THE F.B.I.
NOBODY'S EVER HEARD OF
AN AGENT JAROD JACKSON.

492
00:33:19,098 --> 00:33:22,932
WELL, IT'S A BIG AGENCY.
MAYBE YOU TALKED
TO THE WRONG PERSON.

493
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:25,869
IF ANY OF THOSE PEOPLE
IN THERE DIE,
IT'S ON YOUR HEAD.

494
00:33:25,938 --> 00:33:28,838
YOU UNDERSTAND WHAT THAT
MEANS, TO HAVE SOMEBODY'S
BLOOD ON YOUR HANDS?

495
00:33:28,907 --> 00:33:32,809
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I DO.
AND SO DO YOU.

496
00:33:32,878 --> 00:33:37,681
YOUR DEPUTY TOLD ME ABOUT
THAT HOSTAGE SITUATION A YEAR
AGO AT THE GROCERY STORE.

497
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:39,883
THE WAY YOU LURED THAT
PERPETRATOR INTO THE DOORWAY,

498
00:33:39,952 --> 00:33:43,486
AND HESITATED
TO TAKE THE KILL SHOT.

499
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:48,858
DID HE TELL YOU HOW
THAT SAME HOSTAGE-TAKER
TOOK HIS GUN...

500
00:33:48,927 --> 00:33:51,127
AND SHOT TO DEATH
A 15-YEAR-OLD STOCK BOY?

501
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:55,699
DID HE DESCRIBE THE SICK FEELING
I GET EVERY TIME I SEE THAT
BOY'S PARENTS ON THE STREET?

502
00:33:55,768 --> 00:34:00,803
YOU DID WHAT YOU THOUGHT
WAS THE RIGHT THING TO DO.
AND AN INNOCENT BOY...

503
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:03,807
LOST HIS LIFE.

504
00:34:03,876 --> 00:34:07,644
THAT'S THE BLOOD
I HAVE ON MY HANDS,

505
00:34:07,713 --> 00:34:09,646
<i> AGENT</i> JACKSON.

506
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:23,860
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

507
00:34:41,580 --> 00:34:44,548
<i>CERTAINLY HAS BEEN</i>
<i>A LONG DAY, HASN'T IT?</i>

508
00:34:44,617 --> 00:34:47,851
- AGENT JACKSON.
- I WAS WONDERING IF YOU AND I
COULD HAVE A LITTLE TALK.

509
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,353
OH, WELL, THE TRUTH IS,
I'M LATE FOR A MEETING.
PERHAPS LATER.

510
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:53,856
<i>I KNOW ABOUT THE COVER-UP</i>
<i>CONCERNING JAKE LARSEN'S</i>
<i>CORONARY DISEASE.</i>

511
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:57,728
<i>BUT WHAT COULD AN H.M.O.</i>
<i>POSSIBLY HAVE TO GAIN</i>
<i>BY SUCH A COVER-UP?</i>

512
00:34:57,796 --> 00:35:01,731
<i>I SAW YOU AND DR. FRANKLIN</i>
<i>ARGUING IN THE PARKING LOT.</i>
<i>I KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.</i>

513
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:04,467
<i>WE COULD TALK</i>
<i>ABOUT IT HERE IN PRIVATE,</i>
<i>OR WE COULD GO DOWNTOWN...</i>

514
00:35:04,536 --> 00:35:06,970
AND TALK UNDER THE GLARE
OF THE TELEVISION CAMERAS.

515
00:35:07,039 --> 00:35:09,405
IT'S UP TO YOU.

516
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:13,609
IS IT JUST FOR THE MONEY?

517
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:16,379
OR IS IT
SOMETHING MORE PERSONAL?

518
00:35:16,448 --> 00:35:18,648
I SEE THE WAY YOU AND
DR. FRANKLIN ARE TOGETHER.

519
00:35:24,589 --> 00:35:27,391
MY GIRLFRIENDS AND I...

520
00:35:27,459 --> 00:35:30,727
USED TO DREAM ABOUT
MEETING A DOCTOR.

521
00:35:30,796 --> 00:35:33,063
FALLING IN LOVE,
AND LIVING
HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

522
00:35:33,132 --> 00:35:37,600
I ACTUALLY BELIEVED
THAT'S THE WAY IT WOULD BE
FOR STEPHEN AND ME.

523
00:35:37,669 --> 00:35:41,605
YOUR SIGNATURE IS
ON THE RELEASE FORMS FOR
ALL THE PATIENTS IN QUESTION.

524
00:35:41,674 --> 00:35:44,575
I MADE MY DECISIONS BASED ON
FRANKLIN'S RECOMMENDATIONS.

525
00:35:44,643 --> 00:35:48,678
I LOOKED THE OTHER WAY
IN ONE CASE, NEXT THING
I KNEW, I WAS--

526
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:52,949
ALL FOR MONEY.

527
00:35:53,018 --> 00:35:57,587
FRANKLIN WAS GETTING KICKBACKS
FROM THE H.M.O.'s FOR NOT
DOING EXPENSIVE SURGERIES.

528
00:35:57,655 --> 00:36:00,857
BY DENYING CERTAIN PROCEDURES
TO CRITICALLY ILL PATIENTS,

529
00:36:00,926 --> 00:36:03,793
HE SAVES THE H.M.O.
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS
OF DOLLARS.

530
00:36:03,862 --> 00:36:06,896
AND MAKES A NICE PERCENTAGE.
I SWEAR TO YOU...

531
00:36:06,966 --> 00:36:10,166
I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT
JAKE LARSEN UNTIL HIS SONS
TOOK OVER THE HOSPITAL.

532
00:36:10,235 --> 00:36:13,503
FRANKLIN SAID THAT
YOU QUESTIONED HIM, AND
HE THREATENED TO EXPOSE ME...

533
00:36:13,572 --> 00:36:17,107
IF I SAID ANYTHING, AND--
I WAS AFRAID.

534
00:36:17,176 --> 00:36:21,177
NOT HALF AS AFRAID
AS THOSE PATIENTS
WHO WERE SENT HOME TO DIE.

535
00:36:33,492 --> 00:36:36,827
- THE KEY YOU GAVE ME
DOESN'T WORK.
- REALLY? HUH.

536
00:36:36,895 --> 00:36:39,863
MUST HAVE GIVEN YOU
THE WRONG ONE. HERE,
LET ME TRY THIS ONE.

537
00:36:39,931 --> 00:36:43,200
[ Key Turning Lock ]
YEP. THAT WORKS.
[ Chuckling ]

538
00:36:43,269 --> 00:36:47,036
ANGEL, I'M SORRY I HAD
TO DRAG YOU INTO THIS.

539
00:36:47,105 --> 00:36:49,306
<i> "BABY PARKER."</i>
<i> WH-WHAT WAS THAT?</i>

540
00:36:49,375 --> 00:36:51,241
OH, IT'S NOTHING.

541
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:53,610
- IT LOOKED LIKE
A MEDICAL RECORD.
- IT'S ANCIENT HISTORY.

542
00:36:53,678 --> 00:36:55,878
- IT IS MINE, OR LYLE'S?
- IT DOESN'T MATTER!

543
00:36:58,350 --> 00:37:01,551
TRUST ME. SOME DAY,
WHEN I HAVE MORE TIME,
I'LL EXPLAIN EVERYTHING TO YOU.

544
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:04,220
- BUT RIGHT NOW,
I NEED YOUR GUN.
- MY GUN?

545
00:37:04,289 --> 00:37:06,723
<i>THIS IS ABOUT</i>
<i>THAT HIT OUT ON YOU.</i>

546
00:37:06,792 --> 00:37:10,026
<i> YEAH, THE BASTARDS</i>
<i> ARE CLOSIN' IN.</i>

547
00:37:10,095 --> 00:37:12,862
<i>WHO ORDERED IT?</i>
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

548
00:37:12,931 --> 00:37:16,099
I DO KNOW... THIS...

549
00:37:16,168 --> 00:37:18,935
IS THE ONLY THING
THAT REALLY MATTERS.

550
00:37:19,004 --> 00:37:22,939
IT'S THE FUTURE
OF OUR FAMILY.

551
00:37:23,008 --> 00:37:27,644
<i> IT'S THE HEIR TO</i>
<i> THE PARKER NAME, AND IT'S</i>
<i> GROWING INSIDE BRIGITTE.</i>

552
00:37:27,712 --> 00:37:30,947
<i> THE BABY'LL BE HERE SOON.</i>

553
00:37:34,086 --> 00:37:37,587
- WHAT ELSE CAN I DO?
- WELL, THE KEY IS STILL JAROD.

554
00:37:37,656 --> 00:37:40,923
BRING HIM BACK, AND
IT'LL BE JUST LIKE IT WAS.

555
00:37:49,401 --> 00:37:51,401
<i>[ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>

556
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:55,605
<i>[ Ringing ]</i>

557
00:37:55,674 --> 00:37:59,776
[ Beeping ]
I'M ON MY WAY.

558
00:38:11,957 --> 00:38:14,624
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

559
00:38:46,725 --> 00:38:48,724
<i> [ Phone Ringing ]</i>

560
00:38:49,928 --> 00:38:51,861
YEAH?
DR. FRANKLIN?

561
00:38:51,930 --> 00:38:55,565
AGENT JACKSON. CAM AND
BILLY LARSEN HAVE TAPPED
INTO HOSPITAL RECORDS,

562
00:38:55,633 --> 00:38:59,035
AND ARE TRYING TO FIND
INFORMATION ABOUT PATIENTS
WHO WERE DENIED CARE.

563
00:38:59,103 --> 00:39:00,836
CAN YOU CUT THEM OFF?
WE TRIED.

564
00:39:00,905 --> 00:39:05,208
I SUGGEST I DOWNLOAD EVERYTHING.
I WOULDN'T WANT YOU TO LOSE
ANY PATIENT RECORDS.

565
00:39:05,277 --> 00:39:08,110
NO! NO, I'LL, UH--
I'LL HANDLE THAT.

566
00:39:08,180 --> 00:39:11,347
I-I KNOW WHICH FILES
ARE IMPORTANT. CAN I GET
BACK IN MY OFFICE YET?

567
00:39:11,416 --> 00:39:14,216
I DON'T THINK THAT'S A GOOD
IDEA. THINGS ARE STILL
PRETTY DANGEROUS UP HERE.

568
00:39:14,285 --> 00:39:16,219
I COULDN'T ASSURE YOUR SAFETY.

569
00:39:16,288 --> 00:39:19,189
DR. FRANKLIN?

570
00:39:19,257 --> 00:39:21,891
- DR. FRANKLIN.
- I'M ON MY WAY UP.

571
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:25,528
IF YOU THINK THAT'S BEST.

572
00:39:32,170 --> 00:39:35,037
[ Coughs ]

573
00:39:39,511 --> 00:39:42,812
<i>[ Gunshots ]</i>
<i>[ Glass Breaking ]</i>

574
00:39:45,150 --> 00:39:47,717
- WHAT HAPPENED?
- I WAS SHOT! THE LARSEN BOYS.

575
00:39:47,786 --> 00:39:50,053
THEY'RE CRAZY! THEY'RE
COMING DOWN THE HALLWAY.

576
00:39:50,122 --> 00:39:52,622
<i> THEY SAY THEY KNOW WHO'S</i>
<i> RESPONSIBLE FOR TRYING</i>
<i> TO KILL THEIR FATHER.</i>

577
00:39:52,691 --> 00:39:56,092
I'VE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE.
[ Grunts ]

578
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:58,962
- DOCTOR?
- I CAN'T BREATHE!
[ Panting ]

579
00:39:59,031 --> 00:40:02,165
MY HEART!
[ Groans ]

580
00:40:02,234 --> 00:40:04,567
[ Panting ]
WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?

581
00:40:04,636 --> 00:40:07,804
THE SAME THING THAT YOU
LET HAPPEN TO JAKE LARSEN.

582
00:40:07,873 --> 00:40:09,906
YOU'RE HAVING
A MASSIVE HEART ATTACK.

583
00:40:09,975 --> 00:40:12,509
[ Gasping ]
WHA-- WHAT HAVE
YOU DONE TO ME?

584
00:40:12,577 --> 00:40:15,912
<i> I LACED YOUR KEYBOARD WITH</i>
<i> A TRICYCLIC ANTIDEPRESSANT.</i>

585
00:40:15,981 --> 00:40:18,280
IT'S ABSORBED
THROUGH THE FINGERTIPS.

586
00:40:18,349 --> 00:40:22,018
SPEEDS UP THE HEART'S RHYTHM.
THAT'S WHY I FAKED GETTING SHOT,

587
00:40:22,087 --> 00:40:24,521
TOLD YOU THAT THE LARSEN BOYS
WERE COMING DOWN THE HALLWAY--

588
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:28,191
I WANTED TO SCARE YOU. YOU SEE,
ADRENALINE, IT REALLY INCREASES
THE EFFECTS OF THE DRUG.

589
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:32,028
- [ Gasping ] WHY?
- BECAUSE OF WHAT YOU DID
TO JAKE LARSEN.

590
00:40:32,097 --> 00:40:36,333
BECAUSE OF THE DRUGS YOU GAVE
HIM TO COVER UP THE SYMPTOMS
OF HIS CORONARY DISEASE.

591
00:40:36,401 --> 00:40:38,868
- [ Groaning ] WHO ARE YOU?
- I'M EVERYONE.

592
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:42,339
I'M NO ONE. IF YOU
TELL ME THE TRUTH,

593
00:40:42,407 --> 00:40:45,107
I CAN BRING YOUR HEART
BACK TO NORMAL.

594
00:40:45,176 --> 00:40:47,276
LOOK, WE'RE ALL ON THE SAME
SIDE HERE-- [ Grunting ]

595
00:40:47,345 --> 00:40:49,279
THERE'S NO REASON
TO LET THIS BECOME A PROBLEM.

596
00:40:49,347 --> 00:40:52,482
OH, IT BECAME A PROBLEM
WHEN YOU ALIGNED YOURSELF
WITH AN H.M.O....

597
00:40:52,550 --> 00:40:55,718
THAT CARED MORE ABOUT PROFITS
THAN TAKING CARE OF PATIENTS.

598
00:40:55,787 --> 00:40:58,788
GOD, LARSEN WOULDN'T HAVE
SURVIVED ANOTHER YEAR
NO MATTER WHAT WE DID.

599
00:40:58,857 --> 00:41:00,991
THAT IS NOT THE POINT!
YOU'RE A DOCTOR!

600
00:41:01,059 --> 00:41:03,192
YOUR JOB IS TO GIVE CARE,
NOT TAKE IT AWAY!

601
00:41:03,261 --> 00:41:06,462
- [ Groans In Pain ]
- THAT CYANOSIS MUST REALLY
BE SETTING IN RIGHT NOW.

602
00:41:06,531 --> 00:41:10,333
YOU SHOULD REALLY SEEK
TREATMENT. OR YOU CAN
DIE WITHIN MINUTES.

603
00:41:10,402 --> 00:41:13,402
- PLEASE! PLEASE!
- HOW MANY PEOPLE?

604
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:16,739
HOW MANY PEOPLE DID YOU LET DIE
SO YOU COULD STUFF YOUR POCKETS?

605
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:20,243
[ Grunts ] ALL RIGHT, I TOOK
KICKBACKS FROM THE H.M.O.'s...

606
00:41:20,312 --> 00:41:23,713
<i>TO SEND PATIENTS HOME--</i>
<i>NOW PLEASE, HELP ME!</i>

607
00:41:23,781 --> 00:41:28,752
- PLEASE!
- SORRY, DOC.

608
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:31,220
BUT YOUR CLAIM
HAS BEEN DENIED.

609
00:41:31,289 --> 00:41:34,524
NO! NO.
[ Sobbing, Groaning ]

610
00:41:39,630 --> 00:41:42,098
<i>[ Chattering On Police Radio ]</i>

611
00:41:46,038 --> 00:41:49,539
IS HE REALLY GONNA DIE?
I JUST LACED HIS KEYBOARD
WITH TRIGOXIN.

612
00:41:49,607 --> 00:41:52,709
<i>HE HAS NOTHING MORE THAN</i>
<i>A REALLY BAD CASE OF HEARTBURN.</i>

613
00:41:52,778 --> 00:41:56,078
<i>AND HE'LL PROBABLY</i>
<i>LOSE BLADDER CONTROL</i>
<i>FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.</i>

614
00:41:56,147 --> 00:42:00,015
<i>[ Chattering On Police Radio ]</i>

615
00:42:00,084 --> 00:42:02,085
[ Grunting ]

616
00:42:04,422 --> 00:42:07,490
- [ Sighs ]
-<i> [ Siren Wailing ]</i>

617
00:42:08,927 --> 00:42:10,960
I'M GONNA DROP
SOME OF THE CHARGES
AGAINST THE BROTHERS.

618
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:12,996
LET THE JUDGE
DEAL WITH THE REST.

619
00:42:13,065 --> 00:42:16,666
CONSIDERING THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
I THINK THEY'VE SUFFERED
ENOUGH FOR ONE FAMILY.

620
00:42:16,735 --> 00:42:18,801
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

621
00:42:18,870 --> 00:42:21,103
THANK YOU FOR KEEPING ME
FROM DOING SOMETHING STUPID.

622
00:42:21,172 --> 00:42:25,408
I GUESS WE CAN'T LET
THE MISTAKES OF OUR PAST
RUIN OUR FUTURE.

623
00:42:32,017 --> 00:42:35,251
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME, SHERIFF?

624
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:39,054
EXCUSE ME. ARE YOU
FROM THE CHICAGO OFFICE?

625
00:42:39,123 --> 00:42:41,891
- ARE YOU A REPORTER?
-<i> BLUE COVE GAZETTE.</i>

626
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:43,893
HAVE YOU BEEN INVOLVED
DURING THE ENTIRE CRISIS?

627
00:42:43,962 --> 00:42:46,295
NO, I JUST ARRIVED ON THE SCENE.

628
00:42:46,364 --> 00:42:49,332
THERE WAS ANOTHER NEGOTIATOR
INVOLVED. OUR SOURCE
FROM YOUR CHICAGO OFFICE...

629
00:42:49,401 --> 00:42:52,435
-<i> TELLS US HE WAS AN IMPOSTOR.</i>
- THAT'S WHAT WE'VE BEEN TOLD.

630
00:42:52,504 --> 00:42:54,570
- AND WHERE IS HE?
- NO IDEA.

631
00:42:54,639 --> 00:42:57,707
I DON'T KNOW HOW HE DID IT,
BUT WITNESSES SAY HE REALLY
KNEW WHAT HE WAS DOING.

632
00:42:57,776 --> 00:42:59,809
EXCUSE ME.

633
00:43:03,715 --> 00:43:05,649
IT'S YOUR FAULT
WE MISSED HIM.

634
00:43:08,353 --> 00:43:10,553
<i>[ Mr. Parker ]</i>
<i>NOW DON'T TELL ANYBODY.</i>

635
00:43:10,622 --> 00:43:13,423
LIFE AND DEATH, UNDERSTAND?
SOMEDAY, WHEN I HAVE MORE TIME,
I'LL EXPLAIN EVERYTHING TO YOU.

636
00:43:13,492 --> 00:43:15,458
WELL, THE KEY IS STILL JAROD.

637
00:43:15,527 --> 00:43:19,462
BRING HIM BACK, AND
IT'LL BE JUST LIKE IT WAS.

638
00:43:19,531 --> 00:43:22,399
YOU'RE GONNA BE HELD
ACCOUNTABLE FOR THIS, PARKER.

639
00:43:22,467 --> 00:43:26,336
I KNOW.
LET'S GO HOME.

